<setup>
  <selectFromSequence name="m" from ="2" to="6"/>
  <selectFromSequence name="n" from ="2" to="5" exclude="$m"/>
  <selectFromSequence name="a" from ="1" to="3"/>
  <selectFromSequence name="b" from ="4" to="6"/>

  <function name="f">$m + $n*x^(3/2)</function>
  <derivative name="fP">$f</derivative>
  
  <function name="integrand" variable="y">sqrt(1 + $fP^2)</function>
   
  <math name="intValue" simplify>8/(27*$n^2)*(1 + 9*$n^2*$b/4)^(3/2) - 8/(27*$n^2)*(1 + 9*$n^2*$a/4)^(3/2)</math>

</setup>  

  <p>
    Consider the curve defined by the function
    <me>f(x) = $m + $n x^{3/2}</me>
  </p> 

  <p> 
    Let <m>L</m> be the arc length of the curve between the points <m>($a,$$f($a))</m> and <m>($b,$$f($b))</m>.  Set up, and then evaluate exactly, a definite integral whose value is <m>L</m>.  Enter either <q><m>x</m></q> or <q><m>y</m></q> in the box adjacent to <q><m>d</m></q> to indicate either <q><m>dx</m></q> or <q><m>dy</m></q>.
  </p>
        <p>
          <m>L = \int_a^b </m> <mathInput minWidth="75" name="integrandEntered"/> <m>d</m> <mathInput minWidth="15" name="dWhat"/>
        </p>
        <p>
          where 
          <m>a = </m><mathInput minWidth="30" name="aEntered"/> and <m>b = </m><mathInput minWidth="30" name="bEntered"/>.
          <answer simplifyOnCompare><award><when>$aEntered=$a and $bEntered=$b and $dWhat = x and $integrandEntered=$integrand </when></award></answer>
        </p>

  <p> 
    Evaluating the definite integral using the Fundamental Theorem of Calculus, the exact value of <m>L</m> is 
  </p>
  <p>
    <m>L = </m><answer>$intValue</answer>
  </p>